      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "AL-Mawrid United States Inc demonstrates a high level of organizational transparency and financial health. According to <cite id=\"14\">Charity Navigator</cite>, the organization holds an <cite id=\"14\">overall score of 84.5/100</cite>. Its governance is supported by an <cite id=\"15\">independent board</cite> and a clear <cite id=\"16\">theory of change</cite> that is documented and verified. The organization's ability to maintain <cite id=\"11\">10.9 months of working capital</cite> provides a significant buffer against economic volatility, which is particularly high for an organization of its size."
      ],
      "summary": "AL-Mawrid United States Inc, also known as the Ghamidi Center of Islamic Learning, is an educational institution dedicated to promoting a <cite id=\"1\">rational and objective approach to Islamic education</cite>. Founded in <cite id=\"2\">2014</cite>, the organization focuses on scholarly discourse and global outreach to help individuals explore and practice Islam based on reason. Its primary operations include the <cite id=\"3\">AskGhamidi platform</cite>, live weekend programs, and the <cite id=\"4\">Sohbah Study Circle Program</cite>, which collectively aim to revisit religious thought in a modern context. Financially, the organization reported <cite id=\"5\">total revenue of $816,038</cite> in 2023, with a <cite id=\"6\">program expense ratio of 75.2%</cite>, indicating that a significant majority of its budget is directed toward its core educational mission. The charity maintains a <cite id=\"7\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>, reflecting a commitment to public disclosure. While its primary focus is educational, it facilitates religious giving through a <cite id=\"8\">verified zakat-eligible program</cite> that serves the category of fisabilillah. Despite its global mission, the organization currently exhibits <cite id=\"9\">high domestic burn</cite>, with 75.2% of expenses remaining within the United States, though it does provide <cite id=\"10\">foreign grants totaling $24,815</cite> to international recipients.",
